modules.description: Provides functions to convert between a message pack value and a structured view format, and to reconstruct values using unique identifiers. Works with message pack data and custom view structures for serialization and deserialization. Used to transform binary data into a readable format and back, enabling safe manipulation and reconstruction of complex data.

Provides functions for encoding and decoding data using the MessagePack binary format, supporting integers, strings, lists, and maps. Works with OCaml's native data types including variants, tuples, and polymorphic variants. Enables efficient data exchange between OCaml applications and other systems using the msgpack protocol.

Converts message pack values to and from structured views, using unique identifiers for accurate reconstruction. Supports serialization and deserialization of binary data into readable formats and back. Key data types include message pack values and structured views, with operations for conversion and reconstruction. Example tasks include parsing binary logs into nested records or encoding configuration data into compact binary form.
